headline: TikTok, earnings, markets close for Juneteenth: What to Watch
summary: Market Domination Overtime hosts Josh Lipton and Julie Hyman take a look at what investors will be watching on Thursday, June 19 and Friday, June 20. On Thursday, markets will be closed for Juneteenth. Thursday is also the deadline for TikTok's parent company, ByteDance, to sell the social media app to avoid a ban in the US, although President Trump said on Tuesday he will "probably" extend the deadline again. On Friday, earnings from Accenture (ACN), Kroger (KR), Darden Restaurants (DRI), and CarMax (KMX) will be released ahead of the opening bell. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Market Domination here.
